During the development of this Shopping Cart System, I used AI as a guide to better understand how to structure my program, particularly in applying classes, arrays of objects, and basic validation techniques. I initially had difficulty organizing the flow of the program and ensuring that all requirements were met.

Some of the prompts I used included:
"How to create a Product class in C# with methods"
"How to validate user input using int.TryParse"
"How to implement a shopping cart system with stock checking"
"How to prevent duplicate items in a cart using arrays"
"Why is my grand total incorrect when adding multiple items?"

Through these prompts, I was able to build the code step by step while also reviewing and understanding each part before applying it. At first, I tried to finish a whole working version of the program, but I noticed several issues such as incorrect total computation and a messy console output. Because of this, I continued refining it by improving the computation of the grand total, and making the display more organized and user-friendly.

As of now, I am still improving the program by enhancing the menu layout, and making sure that all validations and requirements align with the given criteria. 
